  All methods now score ~45-47 macro — a 3x improvement over frozen base (15.18)!                                                                                                                  
                                                            
  The fuzzy eval fix was huge — SST-2 went from 0% to 98%, AG News from 0-46% to 88-92%. The routing methods all perform similarly well now:                                                       
                                                            
  - TM 75%: 46.83 — best macro, best WMT scores                                                                                                                                                    
  - Direct BL: 46.69 — best SQuAD (72.2)                    
  - TM 25%: 45.69 — best BoolQ (84.0), most compute-efficient                                                                                                                                      
  - TM 50%: 45.55 — best XSum (28.2), SVAMP (48.0)                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                   
  The active fraction tradeoff is mild: 25% → 75% only changes macro by ~1 point, but 75% is better on translation tasks while 25% is better on QA. This is exactly what TaskMap predicts —        
  different tasks benefit from different amounts of active computation.   
